# Microservice Examples

## When to Use This Skill
- User wants to see real-world code examples of Beamable microservices
- User is building a feature and wants a reference implementation to follow
- User wants progressive examples from basic to advanced

For API signatures, CLI commands, storage setup, and common pitfalls, load the `beam-manage-service` skill first.

## Examples

The following four examples demonstrate increasing complexity: basic endpoints → storage → inventory workflows → external integrations. All code is self-contained — these samples are not available via `beam_get_source`.

### Example 1: Stats and Admin Operations

Demonstrates all four endpoint types, structured responses, batch processing with concurrency control, and Stats API usage.

**Response models:**
```csharp
[Serializable]
public class HealthCheckResponse
{
    public string Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime Timestamp { get; set; }
    public string Version { get; set; }
}

[Serializable]
public class BatchResetScoresResult
{
    public int TotalProcessed { get; set; }
    public int SuccessCount { get; set; }
    public int FailureCount { get; set; }
    public List<string> ErrorMessages { get; set; } = new();
    public List<long> FailedPlayerIds { get; set; } = new();
    public double DurationMs { get; set; }
    public string Status { get; set; }
}
```

**Microservice:**
```csharp
public partial class SampleOne : Microservice
{
    private const int MaxBatchSize = 100;
    private const int ChunkSize = 10;

    // Public: no authentication required
    [Callable]
    public HealthCheckResponse HealthCheck()
    {
        BeamableLogger.Log("HealthCheck called");
        return new HealthCheckResponse
        {
            Status = "healthy",
            Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow,
            Version = "2.0"
        };
    }

    // Player-facing: requires authenticated user token
    [ClientCallable]
    public async Task<StatResponse> GetPlayerScore()
    {
        var userId = Context.UserId;
        try
        {
            var score = await Services.Stats.GetStat(
                StatsDomainType.Game, StatsAccessType.Public, userId, "score");
            var value = string.IsNullOrEmpty(score) ? "0" : score;
            return new StatResponse
            {
                Status = "success", Value = value,
                PlayerId = userId, Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
            };
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            BeamableLogger.LogError($"GetPlayerScore failed for userId={userId}: {ex.Message}");
            return new StatResponse
            {
                Status = "error", Value = "0",
                PlayerId = userId, Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
            };
        }
    }

    // Admin-only: batch reset with chunking, deduplication, and error aggregation
    [AdminOnlyCallable]
    public async Task<BatchResetScoresResult> ResetAllScores(long[] playerIds)
    {
        var stopwatch = Stopwatch.StartNew();
        var result = new BatchResetScoresResult();
        try
        {
            if (playerIds == null || playerIds.Length == 0)
            {
                result.Status = "success";
                return result;
            }

            if (playerIds.Length > MaxBatchSize)
            {
                result.Status = "error";
                result.ErrorMessages.Add($"Batch size {playerIds.Length} exceeds maximum {MaxBatchSize}");
                return result;
            }

            var uniqueIds = playerIds.Distinct().ToList();
            result.TotalProcessed = uniqueIds.Count;

            // Process in chunks to avoid rate-limit spikes
            var allResults = new List<DeleteResult>();
            for (int i = 0; i < uniqueIds.Count; i += ChunkSize)
            {
                var chunk = uniqueIds.Skip(i).Take(ChunkSize).ToList();
                var tasks = chunk.Select(id => DeletePlayerScore(id)).ToList();
                var chunkResults = await Task.WhenAll(tasks);
                allResults.AddRange(chunkResults);
            }

            foreach (var r in allResults)
            {
                if (r.Success) result.SuccessCount++;
                else
                {
                    result.FailureCount++;
                    result.FailedPlayerIds.Add(r.PlayerId);
                    result.ErrorMessages.Add(r.ErrorMessage);
                }
            }
            result.Status = result.FailureCount == 0 ? "success" : "partial";
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            result.Status = "error";
            result.ErrorMessages.Add($"Fatal error: {ex.Message}");
        }
        finally
        {
            stopwatch.Stop();
            result.DurationMs = stopwatch.Elapsed.TotalMilliseconds;
        }
        return result;
    }

    // Admin: set a specific player's score using a request DTO
    [AdminOnlyCallable]
    public async Task<StatResponse> SetPlayerScore(SetScoreRequest request)
    {
        if (request == null || request.PlayerId <= 0)
            return new StatResponse { Status = "error", Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow };

        await Services.Stats.SetStats(
            StatsDomainType.Game, StatsAccessType.Public, request.PlayerId,
            new() { { "score", request.Value } });

        return new StatResponse
        {
            Status = "success", Value = request.Value,
            PlayerId = request.PlayerId, Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
        };
    }

    // Direct endpoint: callable from portal extensions or other microservices
    [ServerCallable]
    public HealthCheckResponse InternalSync() => HealthCheck();

    private record struct DeleteResult(bool Success, long PlayerId, string ErrorMessage);

    private async Task<DeleteResult> DeletePlayerScore(long playerId)
    {
        try
        {
            await Services.Stats.DeleteStats(
                StatsDomainType.Game, StatsAccessType.Public, playerId, ["score"]);
            return new DeleteResult(true, playerId, null);
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            return new DeleteResult(false, playerId, $"PlayerId {playerId}: {ex.Message}");
        }
    }
}
```

**Key patterns:** Input validation and size guards, deduplication, chunked concurrency (`Task.WhenAll` per chunk), per-item error tracking with aggregated results, `Stopwatch` for observability.

